Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity =>
        {
            // Runs when app loses focus (Android OnPause)
        })
        .OnStop(activity =>
        {
            // Runs when app is fully backgrounded (Android OnStop)
        }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app =>
        {
            // Runs when app enters background (iOS)
        }));
#endif
});
```

**Cross-platform alternative:** If you don't need the native callback parameters, you can use the `Window.Stopped` event instead — it maps to `OnStop` on Android and `DidEnterBackground` on iOS automatically:

```csharp
// In App.xaml.cs
protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
{
    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);
    window.Stopped += (s, e) => { /* backgrounded on all platforms */ };
    return window;
}
```

**Key tips:**
- Keep handlers fast (<2s) to avoid ANR on Android or watchdog kills on iOS.
- On Android, the back button can skip `Stopped` and go straight to `Destroying` — save critical state in both.
- `Deactivated`/`OnPause` fires for split-screen or notification shade — it doesn't always mean full backgrounding.
